title: For Sale:  NIGHTHAWK CUSTOM T4
postcontent: Nighthawk Custom is excited not only about the Model T4 for what we designed it as but what the response has been from the consumer market. Designed for concealed carry may be the best of both worlds when it comes to muzzle controllability and magazine capacity in a 1911. The T4 contains some of the most evolutionary features offered by the company. The T4 resembles the popular T3, but on a 3.8" barrel platform. Reliability was the most important consideration when plans for the new pistol began, hence the 3.8" Nighthawk match grade barrel over the more popular but less reliable 3.5" or shorter barrel. Additionally, the Nighthawk Everlast Recoil System was modified to fit into the smaller T4 frame, thus reducing felt recoil and decreasing recovery time between shots. The frame is thinned just like Nighthawk's popular Lady Hawk. The proprietary barrel is crowned and recessed with the slide. On the outside, the front of the slide has cuts designed to reduce weight. They taper in towards the crowned barrel, giving a unique look to the T4 like no other handgun produced by Nighthawk. Grips are like the T3 and are thinned for less bulk. COMES WITH NIGHTHAWK BAG AND 5 EXTRA MAGS

title: For Sale:  1945 CARL GUSTAF AG M/42B "LJUNGMAN" 6.5x55mm SWEDISH RIFLE
postcontent:
ALL ORIGINAL, ALL MATCHING SERIAL NUMBERS. SERIAL # 288*** WHICH IS PART OF THE ORIGINAL CARL GUSTAF BUILD. RIGHT SIDE OF THE RECEIVER RING ARE THE INITIALS OF THE FACTORY INSPECTOR S.S. WHICH DENOTES STEN W. STENMO, WHO SERVED AS AN INSPECTOR AT CARL GUSTAFS FROM 1942-1946. THIS RIFLE IS IN PRISTINE CONDITION. 
The Ag M/42B was designed by Erik Eklund of the AB C.J. Ljungmans Verkstäder company, which is why it’s referred to as the “Ljungman Rifle”. It was manufactured by Carl Gustafs Stads Gevärsfaktori, but was never used in large numbers, so only about 30,000 rifles were made.The left side of the receiver is marked with the serial number, “crown / C” (a Carl Gustafs mark), “1945” (the date of manufacture) and “B” (noting the rifle has been upgraded to a Model B). The left side of the safety lever, buttplate, bottom metal, barrel band, barrel band retainer, nose cap and nose cap retainer are all marked with a “crown”. The left side of the bolt is etched with the serial number. The buttplate is marked with the serial number.
